
Overview of noun sorrow

The noun sorrow has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (3) sorrow -- (an emotion of great sadness associated with loss or bereavement; "he tried to express his sorrow at her loss")
2. (1) sorrow, regret, rue, ruefulness -- (sadness associated with some wrong done or some disappointment; "he drank to drown his sorrows"; "he wrote a note expressing his regret"; "to his rue, the error cost him the game")
3. (1) grief, sorrow -- (something that causes great unhappiness; "her death was a great grief to John")
4. sadness, sorrow, sorrowfulness -- (the state of being sad; "she tired of his perpetual sadness")

